snippet.textDisplay:
To be brutally honest song would have been better if it was only in Urdu. Before every one start being judgmental let me tell you the reason why I think this way.
Ali Zafar proved himself this season that he can sing out of his comfort zone and he speaks English as well. :)
When it comes to singing in English he doesn't have the 'hold' in his voice. At times it sounds like he was concentrating too hard on the pronunciation of the word rather than singing freely. 
I mean, 10 out 10 for the effort but next time please only sing in Urdu or Punjabi.
P.S Ali looks Ramiz Raja from Long Shot. :P
snippet.textOriginal:
To be brutally honest song would have been better if it was only in Urdu. Before every one start being judgmental let me tell you the reason why I think this way.
Ali Zafar proved himself this season that he can sing out of his comfort zone and he speaks English as well. :)
When it comes to singing in English he doesn't have the 'hold' in his voice. At times it sounds like he was concentrating too hard on the pronunciation of the word rather than singing freely. 
I mean, 10 out 10 for the effort but next time please only sing in Urdu or Punjabi.
P.S Ali looks Ramiz Raja from Long Shot. :P
